# <type>(<scope>): <subject> (#<sub-issue-id>)
#   |     |          |         |
#   |     |          |         └─ from docs/DESIGN.md §9 (e.g. #1.3, #5a.2). Optional for chore/deps.
#   |     |          └─────────── imperative, lowercase, ≤ 72 chars, no period
#   |     └────────────────────── mcp · backend · frontend · etl · infra · docs · i18n · community · security · deps
#   └──────────────────────────── feat · fix · docs · refactor · chore · test · perf · build · ci · style · revert
#
# Use `feat!` / `fix!` / `refactor!` (suffix the `!`) for breaking changes;
# also add `BREAKING CHANGE: …` in the footer.
#
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Wrap body at 72 chars. Explain WHY, not WHAT (the diff already shows what).
# Leave a blank line above and below the body.



# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Footer (optional, blank line before):
#   Closes #<gh-issue-number>           — auto-closes the GitHub issue on merge
#   Refs #<gh-issue-number>             — references without closing
#   BREAKING CHANGE: <description>      — paired with `!` in subject
#   Signed-off-by: Name <email>         — DCO (use `git commit -s` to add)
#   Co-Authored-By: Name <email>        — credit pair / AI
#
# Example:
#   feat(mcp): implement list_domains tool (#1.3)
#
#   Returns 20 domains seeded from config/domains.yaml with i18n names
#   and dataset counts. Uses the mcp-core registry pattern that the next
#   4 tools will reuse.
#
#   Closes #3
#   Signed-off-by: hydai <z54981220@gmail.com>
